subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis:
Male pregonite with flat triangular projection in the ventral margin (
Fig. 1D
), postgonite with a short median seta (
Fig. 1D
) and anterior juxtal margin as peculiar folded digitate lobes (
Figs. 1
C-D, 3C, 3E), and vesica with four extensions, X-shaped, in ventral view (
Fig. 1C
). Female T6 divided in two sclerotized plate (
Figs. 2
A-B), T8 absent, ST8 short, with a rounded, setose, and poorly delimited apical area (
Fig. 2A
), and vaginal plate membranous and poorly delimited (
Fig. 2B
).

